    bibo:startPage "78" ;
    bibo:volume "4869" ;
    dc:creator "Buys, Sandor Christiano" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "A study on taxonomy and phylogeny of immature stages of Sphecidae (Hymenoptera: Apoidea)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418362>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418372>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418370>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418366> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418362>
    dc:description "FIGURES 2–8. Larval morphology of species of Sceliphrini. 2, Penepodium luteipenne: part of the labium; 3–5, Podium denticulatum: 3, labrum, frontal view; 4, mandible, basal portion; 5, mandible, apical portion; 6–8, Sceliphron fistularium: 6, head, frontal view; 7, margin of the labrum; 8, antennal orbit. (AO = antennal orbit, LP = labial palpus, P = puncture, PA = parietal band, PB = parietal band, Po = pore, S = seta, SC = sensorial cone, SM = serrated margin of the third mandibular tooth, Sp = spines)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4418362/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418372>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21–25. Larval morphology of Sphecini (S.E.M.). Prionyx thomae: 21, part of the head, showing specially the clypeus; 22, sensorial area of the epipharynx; 23, median portion of the epipharinx; Sphex dorsalis: 24, peritreme and pore of the spiracle; 25, detail of the spines of the spiracle atrium. (AO = antennal orbit, BS = basiconic sensilla, SA = basiconic sensilla of the sensorial area, SS = basiconic sensilla of the superior portion of the epipharynx, TP = anterior tentorial pit)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4418372/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418370>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13–20. Larval morphology of Podium denticulatum (S.E.M). 13, ornamented peritreme of the spiracle; 14, flattened spines in the spiracle atrium; 15, oral portion of the head; 16, lacinial area; 17, detail of the apex of the labrum; 18, maxilla, internal basal view; 19, detail of the labium, ventral view; 20, papillae of the apex of the spinnerets. (BS = basiconic sensilla of the labrum, MS = spinulose margin of the spinneret, SC = sensorial cone)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4418370/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418366>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9–12. Larval morphology of species of Sphecini and Ammophilini. 9, Prionyx thomae: part of the labium; 10, Prionyx fervens: apex of the maxilla; 11–12, Ammophila sp. 1: 11, epipharynx; 12, mandible, frontal view. (MA = internal mandibular articulation, BS = basiconic sensilla, De = area with denticles, G = galea, LP = labial palpus, (MP = maxillary palpus, S = setae SA = basiconic sensilla in sensorial area, SB = basiconic sensilla in marginal band)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4418366/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

